      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be directly traceable to the clinical decision QoI (absolute hemolysis level) rather than surrogate metrics.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed against normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) rather than absolute plasma free haemoglobin. Surrogate metric reduces direct relevance to the device approval QoI."
